interesting_coloumns = ['climate_temperature', 'cmc_0_0_0_2_interpolated', 'cmc_0_0_0_2_next', 'cmc_0_0_0_2', 
                               'gfs_temperature_sea', 'gfs_temperature_sea_interpolated', 'gfs_temperature_sea_next',
                              'wrf_t2', 'wrf_t2_next', 'wrf_t2_interpolated']

def paint_tick(ax, indexes):
    ax.xaxis.set_ticks(indexes)
    ax.set_xticklabels(indexes) 
    for tick in ax.xaxis.get_ticklabels():
        if tick.get_text() in interesting_coloumns:
            tick.set_color('blue')
        elif tick.get_text() in other_columns + climate_columns:
            tick.set_color('orange')

def corr_with_temp(columns_name: str):
    col = [cmc_columns, gfs_columns, wrf_columns][['cmc', 'gfs', 'wrf'].index(columns_name)]
    columns = fact_columns + other_columns + climate_columns + col
    df = train_2018_09.loc[:, columns]
    
    if columns_name == 'cmc':
        df = df.loc[df.cmc_available == 1]
    elif columns_name == 'gfs':
        df = df.loc[df.gfs_available == 1] 
    else:
        df = df.loc[df.wrf_available == 1]
    
    temp_corr = df.corrwith(df.fact_temperature)
    temp_coor_over_zero = temp_corr[temp_corr > 0].sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 2))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    ax.plot(temp_coor_over_zero.index, temp_coor_over_zero)
    plt.title(columns_name, fontsize=16, y=1.05)
    plt.xlabel("features", fontsize=12)
    plt.ylabel("importance", fontsize=12)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
      
    paint_tick(ax, temp_coor_over_zero.index)
    
    plt.show()
    
for columns in ['cmc', 'gfs', 'wrf']:
    corr_with_temp(columns)

In [11]:
IMPORTANCE = 0.05

def draw_cwsm_plot(ax, cwsm_coor, cloudy):
    ax.plot(cwsm_coor.index, cwsm_coor)
    ax.set_title('cloudy = {}'.format(cloudy))
    ax.set_ylim(0, 1)
    paint_tick(ax, cwsm_coor.index)
    plt.setp(ax.xaxis.get_majorticklabels(), rotation=90)

def corr_with_cwsm(columns_name: str):
    col = [cmc_columns, gfs_columns, wrf_columns][['cmc', 'gfs', 'wrf'].index(columns_name)]
    columns = fact_columns + other_columns + climate_columns + col
    df = train_2018_09.loc[:, columns]
    
    if columns_name == 'cmc':
        df = df.loc[df.cmc_available == 1]
    elif columns_name == 'gfs':
        df = df.loc[df.gfs_available == 1] 
    else:
        df = df.loc[df.wrf_available == 1]
    
    cwsm_corr_0 = df.corrwith(df.fact_cwsm_class == 0)
    cwsm_coor_over_zero_0 = cwsm_corr_0[cwsm_corr_0 > IMPORTANCE].sort_values(ascending=False)
    cwsm_corr_10 = df.corrwith((10 <= df.fact_cwsm_class) & (df.fact_cwsm_class < 20))
    cwsm_coor_over_zero_10 = cwsm_corr_10[cwsm_corr_10 > IMPORTANCE].sort_values(ascending=False)
    cwsm_corr_20 = df.corrwith(df.fact_cwsm_class >= 20)
    cwsm_coor_over_zero_20 = cwsm_corr_20[cwsm_corr_20 > IMPORTANCE].sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    f, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))
    f.suptitle(columns_name, fontsize=16, y=1.02)
    
    draw_cwsm_plot(ax[0], cwsm_coor_over_zero_0, 0)
    draw_cwsm_plot(ax[1], cwsm_coor_over_zero_10, 0.5)
    draw_cwsm_plot(ax[2], cwsm_coor_over_zero_20, 1)
    
    plt.show()
    
for columns in ['cmc', 'gfs', 'wrf']:
    corr_with_cwsm(columns)

from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, make_scorer

rmse_score = make_scorer(mean_squared_error, squared=False, greater_is_better=False)

def two_gradus_score(y_true, y_pred):
    x, y = np.array(y_pred), np.array(y_true)
    return ((x - 2 <= y) & (y <= x + 2)).sum() / np.array(y_true).size

from sklearn.dummy import DummyRegressor

scores = pd.DataFrame(columns=['rmse', 'tgs'], index=interesting_coloumns)

def dummy_check(prediction: str):
    df = train_2018_09[['fact_temperature', 'cmc_available', 'gfs_available', 'wrf_available', prediction]]
    df2 = train_2018_10[['fact_temperature', 'cmc_available', 'gfs_available', 'wrf_available', prediction]]
    
    if prediction.startswith('cmc'):
        df = df.loc[df.cmc_available == 1]
        df2 = df2.loc[df2.cmc_available == 1]
    elif prediction.startswith('gfs'):
        df = df.loc[df.gfs_available == 1] 
        df2 = df2.loc[df2.gfs_available == 1] 
    else:
        df = df.loc[df.wrf_available == 1]
        df2 = df2.loc[df2.wrf_available == 1]
        
    dummy = DummyRegressor().fit(df[prediction], df.fact_temperature)
    tgs = two_gradus_score(df2.fact_temperature, dummy.predict(df2[prediction]))
    rmse = mean_squared_error(df2.fact_temperature, dummy.predict(df2[prediction]), squared=False)
    scores.loc[prediction] = [rmse, tgs]
    
for prediction in interesting_coloumns:
    dummy_check(prediction)

def train_test_val(source_name: str, df_train, df_valid):
    start_time = datetime.now()
    regressor = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=35).fit(df_train, train_2018_09.fact_temperature[df_train.index])
    print('Training time:', datetime.now() - start_time)
    
    y_pred = regressor.predict(df_valid)
    rmse = mean_squared_error(train_2018_10.fact_temperature[df_valid.index], y_pred, squared=False)
    tgs = two_gradus_score(train_2018_10.fact_temperature[df_valid.index], y_pred)
    print('Only {} columns give RMSE: {:.6}, TGS: {:.6}'.format(source_name, rmse, tgs))

def train_test_frames(features=[], importance=0, *, dropna=False, climate_one_hot=False):
    if features:
        temp_corr = train_2018_09[features].corrwith(train_2018_09.fact_temperature)
    else:
        temp_corr = train_2018_09.drop(['fact_temperature'], axis=1).corrwith(train_2018_09.fact_temperature)
    
    temp_coor_over_zero = temp_corr[temp_corr > importance].sort_values(ascending=False)
    regressor_features = temp_coor_over_zero.index.to_list()
    
    if climate_one_hot:
        df_train = pd.concat([train_2018_09[regressor_features], climate_ohe9], axis=1)
        df_valid = pd.concat([train_2018_10[regressor_features], climate_ohe10], axis=1)
    else:
        df_train = train_2018_09[regressor_features]
        df_valid = train_2018_10[regressor_features]
    
    if dropna:
        return df_train.dropna(), df_valid.dropna()
    else:
        return df_train, df_valid

def grow_forest(model, title, df_train, df_valid):
    start_time = datetime.now()
    rf_regressor = model.fit(df_train, train_2018_09.fact_temperature[df_train.index])
    print('Training time:', datetime.now() - start_time)

    y_pred = rf_regressor.predict(df_valid)
    rmse = mean_squared_error(train_2018_10.fact_temperature[df_valid.index], y_pred, squared=False)
    tgs = two_gradus_score(train_2018_10.fact_temperature[df_valid.index], y_pred)
    print('{} model gives RMSE: {:.6}, TGS: {:.6}'.format(title, rmse, tgs))

In [36]:
from catboost import Pool

class CatboostQuantizer:
    def __init__(self, border_count=32, method="UniformAndQuantiles"):
        self.border_count = border_count
        self.method = method
        
    def fit(self, df):
        self.train_data = Pool(df)
        self.train_data.quantize(border_count=self.border_count, feature_border_type=self.method)
        self.train_data.save_quantization_borders("borders.dat")
        return self
        
    def transform(self, df):
        f = np.fromfile("borders.dat", sep=' ')
        f_ind, f_val = f[::2], f[1::2]
        bins = pd.DataFrame(index=np.arange(df.shape[1]), columns=np.arange(32))
        
        j, k = 0, 0
        for i in np.arange(f_ind.size):
            if (k != f_ind[i]):
                j = 0
                k += f_ind[i] - k

            bins.loc[f_ind[i], j] = f_val[i]
            j += 1
        
        result_frame = []
        for i in bins.index:
            b = np.array(bins.loc[i], dtype='float64')
            result_frame.append(np.digitize(df.loc[:, df.columns[i]], b, right=True))
            
        return pd.DataFrame(np.array(result_frame).T, columns=df.columns, index=df.index)

IMPORTANCE = 3e-3

def draw_temp_plot(ax, model, model_title):
    try:
        feature_flag = np.where(model.feature_importances_ > IMPORTANCE)        
        feature = np.array([model.feature_names_in_[feature_flag], model.feature_importances_[feature_flag]])
        feature =  feature[:, feature[1, :].argsort()][:, ::-1]
        ax.plot(feature[0], feature[1])
        
    except AttributeError:
        feature = np.array([np.array(model.feature_names_), model.feature_importances_])
        feature[1] = feature[1].astype(np.float64) / np.linalg.norm(feature[1].astype(np.float64))
        feature_flag = np.where(feature[1].astype(np.float64) > IMPORTANCE)
        feature = feature[:, feature_flag[0]]
        feature = feature[:, feature[1, :].argsort()][:, ::-1]
        ax.plot(feature[0], feature[1].astype(np.float64))
    
    ax.set_title(model_title)
    ax.set_ylim(0, 1)
    plt.setp(ax.xaxis.get_majorticklabels(), rotation=90)
    ax.set_xlabel("features", fontsize=12)
    ax.set_ylabel("importance", fontsize=12)

import shap
shap.initjs()

def draw_shap(model, X):
    explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(model)
    shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X)
    shap.summary_plot(shap_values, X, plot_type='bar', plot_size=(8, 8))

def train_test_cwsm(train, onehot):
    frame = pd.concat([train, onehot], axis=1).drop(['climate', 'wrf_available'], axis=1).dropna()
    target = frame.fact_cwsm_class.replace([0, 10, 20, 11, 12, 13, 21, 22, 23], [0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1])
    frame = frame.drop(['fact_cwsm_class', 'fact_temperature'], axis=1)
    return frame, target

df_train, cwsm_train = train_test_cwsm(train_2018_09, climate_ohe9)
df_valid, cwsm_valid = train_test_cwsm(train_2018_10, climate_ohe10)
df_test, cwsm_test = train_test_cwsm(train_2018_11, climate_ohe11)

from sklearn.metrics import balanced_accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score

def classify(model, model_title, df_train, df_valid):
    start_time = datetime.now()
    classifier = model.fit(df_train, cwsm_train)
    print('Training time:', datetime.now() - start_time)
    
    y_pred = model.predict(df_valid)
    b_acc = balanced_accuracy_score(cwsm_valid, y_pred)
    precision = precision_score(cwsm_valid, y_pred, average='weighted')
    recall = recall_score(cwsm_valid, y_pred, average='weighted')
    f1 = f1_score(cwsm_valid, y_pred, average='weighted')
    print("{} model gives balanced accuracy: {:.6}, precision: {:.6}, recall: {:.6}, f1: {:.6}".format(
        model_title, b_acc, precision, recall, f1))

    b_acc, precision, recall, f1))
